detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when the Housekeeping App completes its initialization.
The Version fields contain the HK_MAJOR_VERSION, HK_MINOR_VERSION, HK_REVISION, and HK_MISSION_REV version identifiers.

para.computeroutput: 'Cmd Msg with Invalid command code Rcvd ID = 0x%04X, CC = %d'
'Cmd Msg with Invalid command code Rcvd ID = 0x%04X, CC = %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application receives an unexpected command code

para.computeroutput: 'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%X, CC = %d, Exp Len = %d, Len = %d'
'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%X, CC = %d, Exp Len = %d, Len = %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the actual command length does not equal the expected command length

Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application successfully receives a No-op command. The command is used primarily as an indicator that the HK application can receive commands and generate telemetry.
The Version fields contain the HK_MAJOR_VERSION, HK_MINOR_VERSION, HK_REVISION, and HK_MISSION_REV version identifiers.

Type: DEUBUG
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application receives a Reset Counters command.

para.computeroutput: 'HK table definition exceeds packet length. MID:0x%04X, Length:%d, Count:%d'
'HK table definition exceeds packet length. MID:0x%04X, Length:%d, Count:%d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the received input packet is not large enough to accommodate every entry in the copy table. The count indicates the total number of copy table entries that reference past the end of the input packet.

para.computeroutput: 'HK Processing New Table: ES_GetPoolBuf for size %d returned 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application receives an error when requesting memory from the ES memory pool

'HK Processing New Table:SB_Subscribe for Mid 0x%04X returned 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application receives an error while subscribing to the input messages.

'HK TearDown Old Table: ES_PutPoolBuf for pkt:0x%08X returned 0x%04X'

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the HK application receives an error while attempting to free the memory for an output message

Cause:
